ntage of profitable trades |\n| Profit Factor     | Total profit / total loss |\n\n#### **Python Implementation of Performance Metrics**\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef compute_performance_metrics(trades, returns):\n    \"\"\"\n    Compute key performance metrics for the QA-based trading strategy.\n    \n    :param trades: List of trade profits/losses\n    :param returns: List of daily returns\n    :return: Dictionary with performance metrics\n    \"\"\"\n    win_rate \u003d sum(1 for trade in trades if trade \u003e 0) / len(trades)\n    profit_factor \u003d sum(trade for trade in trades if trade \u003e 0) / abs(sum(trade for trade in trades if trade \u003c 0))\n    \n    sharpe_ratio \u003d np.mean(returns) / np.std(returns) * np.sqrt(252)\n    max_drawdown \u003d np.min(np.cumsum(returns))\n\n    return {\n        \"Win Rate\": win_rate,\n        \"Profit Factor\": profit_factor,\n        \"Sharpe Ratio\": sharpe_ratio,\n        \"Max Drawdown\": max_drawdown\n    }\n\n# Example usage\ntrades \u003d [50, -30, 100, -20, 75, -10]  # Simulated trade profits/losses\ndaily_returns \u003d np.random.randn(252) * 0.01  # Simulated daily returns for 1 year\nmetrics \u003d compute_performance_metrics(trades, daily_returns)\nprint(metrics)\n```\n✅ **Why These Metrics?**\n- Provides **risk-adjusted returns**.\n- Helps **compare strategies over time**.\n- Identifies **drawdown risks before deployment**.\n\n---\n\n## **4. Optimization Techniques for QA-Based Models**\nTo optimize **QA cycle parameters**, we need to **find the best modulus or cycle length** for market trends.\n\n### **Techniques**\n✅ **Grid Search Optimization** (Brute-force)\n✅ **Bayesian Optimization** (Smart adaptive tuning)\n✅ **Genetic Algorithms** (Evolutionary cycle discovery)\n\n#### **Optimizing Cycle Length using Grid Search**\n```python\nfrom itertools import product\n\ndef optimize_modulus(prices, modulus_range):\n    \"\"\"\n    Find the best modulus parameter for QA-based cycle detection.\n  